title: Slow Cooker Fiesta Chicken & Rice Bowls
directions: Spray your Crock Pot with non-stick spray and add the chicken, rice, enchilada sauce, green chilies, chicken broth, onion, cumin and salt. Stir to combine and cook on low for 5-6 hours or high for 3-4 hours. Serve topped with pico de gallo, queso fresco and Greek yogurt.
ingredients: OPTIONAL - 1 c. non-fat plain Greek yogurt or light sour cream
